According to the information presented, ABC Corp. has a more mechanical organizational structure. A mechanistic organization is extremely centralized and structured. It is highly formalized, with stringent rules and procedures governing employee conduct. It has a defined division of work and strong staff specialization. ABC Corp. has a CEO and a few people under him. The corporation has strict protocols and job definitions, and low-level workers have minimal decision-making power. This denotes an organized, regimented corporation. It also denotes a specialist corporation with clear division of work. Organic organizations are decentralized, flatter, and more adaptable. It is autonomous and informal. It also emphasizes cross-functional cooperation and agile decision-making. Accordingly, ABC Corp. is mechanical. Mechanistic structures provide for clear lines of authority, established processes, and efficient resource usage in stable environments. 